@SGeetansh Anytime you see a case like this where there is both a `setup.py` and `setup_common.py` in the same directory. Add

```python
REQUIREMENTS_TXT_PATH = Path(SELF_PATH, "requirements.txt")
if REQUIREMENTS_TXT_PATH.is_file():
    common.KWARGS["install_requires"] += list(
        map(lambda i: i.strip(), REQUIREMENTS_TXT_PATH.read_text().split("\n"))
    )
```

to the `setup_common.py`

Remove anything that has been added to `install_requires` within `setup.py` or `setup_common.py` and put it in `requirements.txt`. **Do not** modify or remove the code related to `dffml` or `dffml-*-*` which will look like this:

```python
(
    ["dffml>=0.3.7"]
    if not any(
        list(
            map(
                os.path.isfile,
                list(
                    map(
                        lambda syspath: os.path.join(
                            syspath, "dffml.egg-link"
                        ),
                        sys.path,
                    )
                ),
            )
        )
    )
    else []
)
```
